A police officer was killed and 15 others injured when their Armoured vehicle rolled along Elwak- Kutulo road in Mandera. The vehicle was speeding when the driver lost its control during heavy rains yesterday afternoon. The injured have been moved to various hospitals for treatment. On August 3, the terrorists killed a police officer and seriously injured another in daring simultaneous attacks on two police camps in Lafey, Mandera county. They also destroyed four police cars and a telecommunications must. In July last year, at least six people were killed when suspected al Shabaab militants sprayed two buses with bullets between Wargadud and Elwak in Mandera. More on this: Cop missing after suspected al Shabaab attack in Mandera